                            <comment id="13924318" author="rhatch" created="Fri, 7 Mar 2014 20:47:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;attaching patch&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13924464" author="benedict" created="Fri, 7 Mar 2014 23:09:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Actually it looks like this was a minor bug - it should accept both commands. Had a quick look and this was only functioning for printing of help, not for running the commands, which was a bit of a mistake. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Attached a patch that fixes this, and also adds a line stating &quot;help &amp;lt;command&amp;gt;&quot; right at the top, as I had a number of queries from people about how on earth it worked that were mostly solved by giving them that command; it&apos;s not obvious from its position in the normal print out that it would be so useful.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13933670" author="jbellis" created="Thu, 13 Mar 2014 18:09:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;(&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=xedin&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;xedin&quot;&gt;xedin&lt;/a&gt; to review)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13933853" author="benedict" created="Thu, 13 Mar 2014 18:37:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=xedin&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;xedin&quot;&gt;xedin&lt;/a&gt; I&apos;ve pushed a &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/belliottsmith/cassandra/tree/iss-6824&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;branch&lt;/a&gt; merged with &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-6835&quot; title=&quot;cassandra-stress should support a variable number of counter columns&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-6835&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-6835&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; to make things easier for you, as they would conflict.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
